
[1]soldier

   SOLDIER, n. soljur. [from L. solidus, a piece of money, the pay of a
   soldier.]

   1. A man engaged in military service; one whose occupation is military;
   a man enlisted for service in an army; a private, or noe in the ranks.
   There ought to be some time for sober reflection between the life of a
   soldier and his death.

   2. A man enrolled for service, when on duty or embodied for military
   discipline; a private; as a militia soldier.

   3. Emphatically, a brave warrior; a man of military experience and
   skill, or a man of distinguished valor. In this sense, an officer of
   any grade may be denominated a soldier.
